Atlas Mining, Globe Telecom, Splash: Philippines Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-07-05T00:47:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-05/atlas-mining-globe-telecom-splash-philippines-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.6 percent to
4,421.56.  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp: The
company’s Carmen mine shipped $24.54 million of copper and gold
last month, a stock exchange filing showed. The shares climbed
1.7 percent to 21.60 pesos.  Globe Telecom Inc. (GLO)  : The nation’s second-largest
provider of mobile phone services supports a government plan to
cut interconnection fees, or charges collected from consumers
reaching users in other networks, the Philippine Daily Inquirer
reported, citing Froilan Castelo, a counsel at Globe. Castelo
couldn’t be reached in his office for comment.  The stock gained 0.2 percent to 887 pesos.  Philippine Long
Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  , owner of the nation’s biggest
provider of mobile phone services, increased 0.7 percent to
2,396 pesos.  Splash Corp. (SPH)  : The maker of whitening soap bought
back 4.52 million shares at 2.20 pesos, a stock-exchange filing
showed. The stock was unchanged at 2.22 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
